[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Okay, so how many times have you rebuilt the exact same back end? CRUD, off, admin panel, file uploads. A lot of the time what looks like building is usually just rebuilding. What if you could point one tool at your existing SQL database and get a full back end? That\'s'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Directus, a real-time API and app dashboard for managing SQL database content. A lot of devs are starting to realize they\'ve been doing it this the hard way the whole time. Let me show you how all this works in just a few'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'minutes. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; The biggest back end problem for most of us isn\'t complexity, it\'s repetition. We\'re not solving new problems, we\'re'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'wiring the same code again and again, and that really just eats into our time. Directus cuts all that out. It connects straight to your Postgres, MySQL, or Oracle database. No migrations, no rebuilding your whole schema somewhere'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'else. We instantly get REST and GraphQL APIs, field-level permissions, real-time subscriptions, flow and automations, file handling, and a clean admin UI. Now, the cool part here is your database'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just stays. It\'s not some duplicate layer. That matters way more than it sounds. Now, let me show you. If you enjoy open source tools and coding tips to speed up your workflow, be sure to subscribe. We have videos coming out all'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the time. All right, now starting from absolute zero with a clean Directus install, no database tables, nothing preloaded, just a completely blank canvas after I already made an account'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here. And instead of connecting to something that already exists, I\'m going to build a full order management app in just a minute or so. First, I create a collection, and I\'ll just name it'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'orders, just like this. That\'s it. Now, the app has a place to store data, and we can add more details into it now. I\'m going to select and override the ones we need here, so things like customer,'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'date, really all that fun stuff. Then, I can manually add in any we would think we would need for something like this. So, I could say customer name, email, product as a drop down,'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'where I can add a key and a value. I can do that for amount and status. Each field adds more detail about the data that we\'re going to store. And notice what\'s missing here. Well, it\'s SQL. There is no SQL. There\'s no migrations.'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'There\'s no switching tabs to write a schema file. It just saves right here in Directus immediately. Now, I can just jump into the content view and start adding orders. So, I can add the first'

[02:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'order here, just a dummy account. I\'ll add another one, and then we can add a third one, right? We have three different orders right here in the system. Now, I have some real data here that we can start to play'

[02:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with. But right now, it\'s wide open, which means anyone could do anything. So, let\'s fix that. How do we fix that? Well, with permissions. So, I go to the public role. I\'m going to find that collection we made orders. We can turn'

[02:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'read on, and I\'m going to make sure everything else here is turned off. So, create, update, delete, those are all gone. Now, it\'s more controlled and safer for what we want. Okay, here is'

[03:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'where it starts to get really cool cuz we can do some automation and build out flows surrounding this. I\'m going to go over here, and I\'m going to create a new flow. I\'m just going to name it something really simple. What is this?'

